        title: 'Closing thoughts',
        text: 'Mindful breathing can change your life, but only if you actually do it. You do not have to reach mastery. Do what you can. Ten minutes of clumsy practice beats not trying at all. Of course, you can learn a lot from experts and take many courses, but the practices will only work once you make them your own. The process of meditation is unique to each person. You and your experience are your main teachers. Only you can motivate yourself and spark real change. Take control of your breath and let that control reach into every part of your life. Try new techniques, mix them up, and follow what feels right. You are the only one who knows what is best for you.\n\nDo not treat breathing as a complicated ritual. You can try it right now. Inhale deeply and exhale slowly. The best breathing practice is the one you do often. Life is often complicated and unpredictable, but breathing is simple. It is the very first step from which you can build something bigger. No matter what you face, remember that you can always lean on your breath and come back to yourself.\n\nA small step to try. Find a scent that strengthens you and weave it into your morning. If you like the smell of lime, dry the peels and use them during breathing practices. Write down your main intention. List all your goals and desires and see what they have in common. Find someone with a positive experience in breathing and meditation, and learn from their journey. If you have read this far, the work has already started.'
